                                        <p>Commercial Vehicles Insurance is a policy that covers the commercial vehicles of a business against external damages, and personal and third party liability. It can be taken for any passenger or goods carrying vehicle, taxis and other miscellaneous vehicles like tractor, crane and. trailers. Third Party Insurance is a statutory requirement under the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988.</p>
