                                        <h2 class="heading-tertiary mb-1">Buying Factors</h2>
                                        <p class="blue-text font-medium">Following factors help determine if you need a Personal Auto Insurance or Commercial Vehicle Insurance</p>
                                        

                                        <ul class="list-disc leading-loose ml-12">
                                            <li><strong>Owner and driver of the vehicle</strong> If the vehicle is owned by any kind of business, then it is likely to be covered under a commercial auto insurance policy.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Usage of vehicle:</strong> When the insured uses the vehicle for business purposes, then he needs a commercial vehicle policy.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Type and Weight of the Vehicle:</strong>  If the vehicle is heavier than a normal size pickup or SUV such as a dump truck, tow truck, semi-truck or commercial trailer, then one definitely needs a commercial auto insurance policy.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Required Business Liability Limits:</strong>  For higher business liability limits, you need a commercial auto insurance policy.</li>
                                        </ul>
